<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SPICER 14-INCH (355.6 MM) STAMPED ANGLE-SPRING CLUTCH - TRANSMISSION INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>TRANSMISSION INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>Observe the following notes and cautions when installing the transmission. Shift the transmission into
            gear. Check wear on fingers of clutch release yoke, cross shaft and cross shaft bushings. Replace yoke, if
            necessary.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Be sure the release bearing yoke clears the bearing and is rotated over the wear pads as the
                transmission is moved forward (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100345">Figure 45</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100346">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the splines by turning the transmission output shaft. Do not force the transmission
                into the clutch or flywheel housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100346">Figure 46</hotlnk>). If it does not enter freely, investigate the cause of the
                problem.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100345" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100345" filename="../figg11/g1100345.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Transmission Installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100346" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100346" filename="../figg11/g1100346.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 46. Transmission Installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100347" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100347" filename="../figg11/g1100347.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 47. Transmission Installation</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Don't let the transmission drop or hang unsupported in the driven discs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100347">Figure 47</hotlnk>). Install transmission mounting bolts, torque to proper
                specs and attach linkage. You are now ready to adjust the clutch.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
